Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and ketonuria, suggesting impaired renal function with possible acute or chronic kidney disease and metabolic stress. Urine is abnormal in appearance and color, with low specific gravity, indicating possible tubular dysfunction. HbA1c is low, excluding chronic hyperglycemia. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further assessment of renal function and underlying causes.
